{"componentChunkName":"component---src-components-blogs-blog-detail-js","path":"/blog/ui-designing-for-iphone-x","result":{"pageContext":{"post":{"id":"9e6b3912-9fac-5532-b26c-01763081e0c1","title":"UI Designing for iPhone X","excerpt":"Design tips from UI perspective while making an app for iPhone X.","_rawBody":[{"_key":"ddc9337cb4ff","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"ddc9337cb4ff0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"iPhone X Screen Size"}],"markDefs":[],"style":"h3"},{"_key":"c0076d24a11d","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"c0076d24a11d0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"To design for iPhone X, let‚Äôs know the details about its screen size first."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"08095982eae5","_type":"customImage","asset":{"_ref":"image-5aa9237bdea838a8005811d822bf69fe2ce3fa20-576x377-png","_type":"reference"}},{"_key":"b97ca0aa4de7","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"b97ca0aa4de70","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"In portrait orientation, the width of the display on iPhone X matches the width of the 4.7\" displays of iPhone 6, iPhone 7, and iPhone 8. The display on iPhone X, however, is 145pt taller than a 4.7\" display, resulting in roughly 20% additional vertical space for content."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"Separatorr":true,"_key":"9dede2824bcd","_type":"separator"},{"_key":"b1d07f05f827","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"b1d07f05f8270","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Image Assets"}],"markDefs":[],"style":"h3"},{"_key":"105afd178784","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"105afd1787840","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"iPhone X has a high-resolution display with a scale factor of @3x. So our icons with @3x rendering are used by iPhone X. Also, its noteworthy that Apple recommends to provide resolution-independent PDFs."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"Separatorr":true,"_key":"26daf2dcd974","_type":"separator"},{"_key":"f169d1b5f5d6","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"f169d1b5f5d60","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"iPhone Aspect Ratio"}],"markDefs":[],"style":"h3"},{"_key":"c8335367f868","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"c8335367f8680","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"iPhone X has a different aspect ratio than 4.7\" iPhones"}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"f077efe82d85","_type":"customImage","asset":{"_ref":"image-5911724238111af8ce44a64904456b260585eed3-576x271-png","_type":"reference"}},{"_key":"88526c27991b","_type":"customBlockQuote","customblockArray":[{"_key":"221ce26aa50b","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"221ce26aa50b0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Background graphics designed for iPhone 8‚Äôs 16:9 aspect ratio will be cropped along the left and right edges on iPhone X if they‚Äôre scaled to fill, or letter-boxed if scaled to fit. Similarly, background graphics designed for iPhone X, will either be cropped along the top and bottom edges on iPhone 8 or pillar-boxed. "},{"_key":"221ce26aa50b1","_type":"span","marks":["strong"],"text":"It‚Äôs best to compose images so that critical visual information remains visible regardless of the iPhone display‚Äôs aspect ratio."},{"_key":"221ce26aa50b2","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"\n"}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"}]},{"Separatorr":true,"_key":"29ba24de0d6d","_type":"separator"},{"_key":"251dada6d1a8","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"251dada6d1a80","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"The Safe Area"}],"markDefs":[],"style":"h3"},{"_key":"398e10621f8d","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"398e10621f8d0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"While designing for iPhone X, one thing to ensure is that the layouts fill the screen and aren‚Äôt obscured by the device‚Äôs rounded corners, sensor housing, or the indicator for accessing the Home screen"}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"0ffe531edc62","_type":"customImage","alt":"These corners should be taken the most care of","asset":{"_ref":"image-da5506d0906f720bf17be11bd61166c3f69d2ad7-576x767-png","_type":"reference"},"imageFigcaptionName":"These corners should be taken the most care of"},{"_key":"207f16eb8540","_type":"customImage","alt":"safe area for iPhone 8","asset":{"_ref":"image-86350985915ed039219320b45a0d1c984b58b7e4-576x886-png","_type":"reference"},"imageFigcaptionName":"safe area for iPhone 8"},{"_key":"cc31dcefa460","_type":"customImage","alt":"safe area for iPhone X","asset":{"_ref":"image-d406d1eb9da0435539ccaca558bca327d2930971-576x722-png","_type":"reference"},"imageFigcaptionName":"safe area for iPhone X"},{"_key":"b16f6192acb9","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"b16f6192acb90","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Make sure, your content is centered and symmetrically inset so it looks great in any orientation and isn‚Äôt clipped ‚õë"}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"29022af8a614","_type":"customImage","alt":"This is how we will use Safe area in interface builder in xcode 9","asset":{"_ref":"image-d81cd3d33207ad16995ba40cf597331695ed23b2-576x326-png","_type":"reference"},"imageFigcaptionName":"This is how we will use Safe area in interface builder in xcode 9"},{"_key":"fd98c75ea4bb","_type":"customBlockQuote","customblockArray":[{"_key":"52a64d00fd8d","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"52a64d00fd8d0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"One thing to note here is that once you check the Safe Area Layout Guide, all your constraints will be added with respect to the safe area and not the superview."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"efea89bd8114","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"efea89bd81140","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Also, It is not at all advisable to hide status bar in iPhone X, as the status bar occupies an area of the screen your app probably won‚Äôt fully utilize."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"}]},{"_key":"64fae4fd6a0c","_type":"customImage","asset":{"_ref":"image-957403c8f59f9c17cb3ff52475004c797ffb848c-576x101-png","_type":"reference"}},{"Separatorr":true,"_key":"d2f9fc084f02","_type":"separator"},{"_key":"505dc34b7ec1","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"505dc34b7ec10","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Gestures"}],"markDefs":[],"style":"h3"},{"_key":"36b3a020a7d9","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"36b3a020a7d90","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"The display on iPhone X uses screen-edge gestures to provide access to Home screen, app switcher, Notification Center, and Control Center."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"2f2469f4399b","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"2f2469f4399b0","_type":"span","marks":["strong"],"text":"Use edge protect:"},{"_key":"2f2469f4399b1","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" If your application might require custom screen-edge gestures that take priority over the system‚Äôs gestures ‚Äî the first swipe invokes the app-specific gesture and a second-swipe invokes the system gesture. This behavior (known as "},{"_key":"2f2469f4399b2","_type":"span","marks":["em"],"text":"edge protect"},{"_key":"2f2469f4399b3","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":") should be implemented."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"Separatorr":true,"_key":"63865cdd2ca0","_type":"separator"},{"_key":"17280bb4f5fc","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"17280bb4f5fc0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Be mindful about these üìù"}],"markDefs":[],"style":"h3"},{"_key":"af23cb52b68a","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"af23cb52b68a0","_type":"span","marks":["em"],"text":"Don‚Äôt duplicate system-provided keyboard features"}],"level":1,"listItem":"bullet","markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"2e4756e97f72","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"2e4756e97f720","_type":"span","marks":["em"],"text":"Avoid placing interactive controls at the very bottom of the screen and in corners"}],"level":1,"listItem":"bullet","markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"82ac95b5b583","_type":"customImage","alt":"Don‚Äôt mask or call special attention to key display features ‚Äî Don‚Äôt attempt to hide the device‚Äôs rounded corners, sensor housing, or indicator for accessing the Home screen by placing black bars at the top and bottom of the screen.","asset":{"_ref":"image-d3afeb83634b7f4aa8fa3cac8b9de96934288e9e-576x349-png","_type":"reference"},"imageFigcaptionName":"Don‚Äôt mask or call special attention to key display features ‚Äî Don‚Äôt attempt to hide the device‚Äôs rounded corners, sensor housing, or indicator for accessing the Home screen by placing black bars at the top and bottom of the screen."},{"_key":"b4da187230dc","_type":"customImage","alt":"Vertically scrollable views, such as tables or collection views, should extend all the way to the bottom of the display rather than being constrained by the Safe Area","asset":{"_ref":"image-86f1b94671ec075cc9947cdd069a09ddfe72e09c-576x711-png","_type":"reference"},"imageFigcaptionName":"Vertically scrollable views, such as tables or collection views, should extend all the way to the bottom of the display rather than being constrained by the Safe Area"},{"_key":"cfc11f245e2e","_type":"customImage","alt":"For adaptive Layout use hidden property based on size classes variation introduced in xcode 9","asset":{"_ref":"image-1a9a3b48e3a3d2f5e67ab7af3a9c6f8b3b17d375-576x267-png","_type":"reference"},"imageFigcaptionName":"For adaptive Layout use hidden property based on size classes variation introduced in xcode 9"},{"Separatorr":true,"_key":"f7c11331d2c2","_type":"separator"},{"_key":"4784988df9e3","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"4784988df9e30","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Source"}],"markDefs":[],"style":"h4"},{"_key":"df7a07b9b75f","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"df7a07b9b75f0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":""},{"_key":"df7a07b9b75f1","_type":"span","marks":["7156a12762c9"],"text":"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/fall2017/201"},{"_key":"df7a07b9b75f2","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":""}],"level":1,"listItem":"bullet","markDefs":[{"_key":"7156a12762c9","_type":"link","href":"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/fall2017/201/"}],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"b3c8c6c5ca43","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"b3c8c6c5ca430","_type"